<br>
I think PvP on the blue servers would be fun, but shouldn't be a permanent choice. <br>
<br>
What are your thoughts on these Blue server PvP options and What ways could these be abused? <br>
<br>
<br>
1. A Priest of Discord quest to turn off the PvP flag. made very simple, costs a few plat, not too much, mabe 50p, possibly an idol made using tradeskills (Idol of Order). You would have to find a Priest of Discord to both enable and disable your PvP flag. There would be a minimum amount of time to wait between flag changes, say 1 game day (3hours) or one earth day (24 hours) All other PvP rules on blue servers would still apply. <br>
<br>
2. PvP zones. Turn some of the underutilized zones into PvP zones. People in your group(raid) would be immune to PvP damage from other group(raid) members. Put something worth fighting for in these zones.<br>
<br>
3. Can't think of another option, but there has got to be one.<br>
<br>
I think a little PvP action would be fun on the blue servers. That's just me, any thoughts? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2cmg5/nexbanner2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
