<br>
We found that on Firiona Vie things are quite different.  You can't really do all out pvp, but the grouping restrictions and xp penalties (for evil grouping with good, etc.) were interesting.  A bunch of us started alts there and had a bunch of fun playing out our own storylines.  But still, pvp is really not there which is too bad.<br>
<br>
I have one pvp player on the blue server I play on (Tholuxe Paells).  He is a level 5 ranger named Goradin who I started as pvp for role-playing reasons.  However because of the pvp restrictions on blue servers, like nobody who is not pvp can buff you, he is kinda useless for regular xp gains with groups.  So he is my brownie hunter, tracking brownies and collecting brownie parts in Greater Faydark for my cake-making business.<br>
<br>
